summary: An ordinance amending Section 4 of Ordinance No. 15585, entitled: "An ordinance granting to the Seattle Electric Company, its successors and assigns, a franchise to construct, maintain and operate a street railway, upon certain parts of Taylor Avenue, other streets, avenues and places in the City of Seattle", passed by the City Council of the City of Seattle on March 4, 1907 and became an ordinance pursuant to Section 16 of Article 4 of the City Charter, March 18, 1907.
